shop.title: Fidel Verdin
shop.description: Fidel Verdin is an award-winning visionary who is an influencer in transformative Hip Hop Education and also cultural community activation. He has two decades of experience as an independent teaching artist and social entrepreneur. Fidel also is trained in group facilitation, strategic graphic communications and conflict resolution. ​ Born and raised in Milwaukee, WI, he developed two former vacant lots into award winning community garden and public art spaces, received the' Most Creative use of Space' award from Groundworks Milwaukee Chapter. Known for his strong focus on team building and sustainability, he specializes in collective impact, social engagement strategies and raising funds. Fidel has received State and Citywide proclamations, awards and acknowledgments for launching 'Summer of Peace' a city wide youth rally promoting community unity and positive edutainment. In addition to maintaining several of his own personal media and art related projects, Fidel Verdin serves as Co-Executive Director at the TRUE Skool, Milwaukee's Center for Transformational Creative Arts and Hip Hop Culture. ​ He is a writer, producer, recording and performing Hip Hop artist known professionally as 'Viva Fidel' and has releases available on all digital streaming services. Fidel has hosted his own talk radio and online shows with over 50,000 downloads and has performed with major artists nationally. ​ His visual art has been exhibited in galleries in Milwaukee as well as Chicago. He is the recipient of a 'Best Experimental Short Film' award from New York International Film Fest and the Wisconsin Giraffe Award given to those that stick their necks out for children in need. Fidel is also the proud Father of two amazing little ones!

shop.title: Spinafexx
shop.description: Milwaukee artists

shop.title: Blanche Brown
shop.description: Blanche Brown’s stepfather Robert Bonner was a talented artist and graphic designer. Only after his death did she realize that art was a valuable vehicle for dealing with loss, giving her a very tangible connection to memory and experience. Blanche is a trained therapist who believes in the power of art to heal, support those affected by trauma, and foster self-awareness of one’s identity. Brown is an art and community activist whose work addresses social injustices and the psychological and psychosocial impact these issues have on undeserved and underrepresented groups. Her artwork provides a forum for youth, women, minorities, and diverse individuals to openly discuss the challenges they encounter. She has been a professional artist for over 18 years. She had exhibited both locally and nationally, as well as a been a guest artist and artist-in-residence at several schools and community programs. Brown is a certified Yoga instructor who incorporates mindfulness and meditation to encourage a grounded perspective and lifestyle. She is a speaker and workshop presenter. She is also a public speaker and workshop presenter.

shop.title: Kristen Kieckhaefer
shop.description: Kristen Kieckhaefer (pronounced KEY-kay-fur) is a Milwaukee-based creator who specializes in live speed painting and drawing entertainment as well as live music performances for a variety of events. This digital art gallery will showcase Kristen's speed paintings as well as her personal artwork. When she’s not making art or music, she enjoys rock climbing, spending quality time with family and friends, and hanging with her two cats, Ember and Willow. Check out her speed art at elevatedeventart.com.

shop.title: Lauren Zens
shop.description: After graduating from Columbia College Chicago in 2012 with a BA in Music Business, Lauren returned to her roots in Milwaukee in 2013. Her interest in contemporary abstract and geometric art started in 2008 with a hard-edge assignment during a high school painting class. Her Golden acrylic paint, 3M blue painter’s tape, and a quilting ruler are now her most cherished tools. Lauren landed her first solo exhibit in 2013 in Chicago and her art-making progressed from there. Greeted with a thriving arts community upon her homecoming to Milwaukee, she's gained exposure in the local market, showing her artwork at bars, boutiques, and galleries. As Lauren’s goals have accelerated toward a full-time career, Lauren spends her free time painting as a creative and therapeutic outlet. Lauren received her MA in Community Arts from Eastern Illinois University in 2019. Her graduate research focused on three primary topics: equitable and inclusive community engagement, maximum learning for under-resourced youth, and the opportunity for progressive, student-centered learning to transform the current landscape of education. Lauren has spent 15 years working with youth of various ages, backgrounds, and abilities, and hopes to use her master’s degree to support multidisciplinary, exploratory, community-based arts opportunities for youth and families.

shop.title: Faith Hildebrand
shop.description: Faith Hildebrand is a multidisciplinary artist, currently based in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. She is primarily making art within the realms of textiles, painting, mixed media, and sculpture. Faith grew up and spent her early life in rural Central Ohio before moving to Milwaukee to pursue her BFA at the Milwaukee Institute of Art and Design. Growing up in an environment where she was always surrounded by and had access to nature, she now feels a strong personal connection with the natural world. It is because of this that much of her work is made with nature and the world around us in mind, while also exploring ideas surrounding physicality, tactility, and material exploration. In making her work, Faith is constantly striving to explore what textiles as a medium can do and where they can be pushed farther.

shop.title: Carley Knight
shop.description: Carley Knight is an emerging artist who works in a wide range of media, from painting with acrylics to metals and ﬁbers. She lives and works in Milwaukee, WI where she was born and raised. Carley has been interested in art for as long as she can remember. When she was a child the answer to the question of what she wanted to be when she grew up was always an artist. Carley attended the UWM Peck School of the Arts starting in 2011, but left early and is mostly self-taught in painting. She was selected to participate in the 2015-16 MARN mentors program and was paired with the renowned folk artist Della Wells. The mentor/mentee exhibition took place at the VAR Gallery in Milwaukee in 2016. Ms. Knight has been in a number of exhibitions. Carley ﬁrst exhibited her paintings during Bay View Gallery night at the Magnet factory in 2016. She has participated in numerous shows, most recently in 2019 at the Hangout Milwaukee cafe. She has sold her art in a variety of locations in and around the Milwaukee area. Ms. Knight is always looking for new opportunities to show her work. She was accepted to be one of the artisans at the Milwaukee Makers Market in August of 2020.

shop.title: Mitzi Romero
shop.description: 21 year old student who is going as a Bilingual Office Tech, while working in a clinic and with CopyWrite as a photographer. I love to dance, read, and paint. When it comes to my photography, I express my feelings through out the pictures. I would like the people to feel and see what the models are feeling, and have the audience read the significance behind the picture.

shop.title: Phoenix Brown
shop.description: Phoenix S. Brown is a Cincinnati-native interdisciplinary artist based in Milwaukee, WI. She holds a BFA in New Studio Practice from the Milwaukee Institute of Art & Design with a minor in Art History. She has exhibited work locally and nationally, and engages in residencies and fellowships. With her influences of fashion, nature, and young adult fiction, interdisciplinary painting grants Brown the space to highlight dialogues around cultural bias, power structures, and inner thinking. She is currently Abert Family Curatorial Fellow at the Milwaukee Art Museum.

shop.title: Jazmyn Williams
shop.description: The memory that will haunt my nightmares is the sight of my father standing on his porch with his hands in his pockets watching my mom and I drive away as the sun went down, the sound of them yelling at each other still fresh in my mind, the smell of dinner burning on the stove, the feeling of hands against the cold glass of the car window trying to reach my father, my breath fogging up the window. I wanted us to be a family. I wanted my parents to be together like they were once before. I abandoned that idea a long time ago, the idea of us being the “ideal”, family or me being the ideal child. I chose to hide away my feelings and never let them resurface, they had no place in the outside world. Everyone finger painted in elementary school and everyone did a blind drawing or two, but art was more than just another class to me. I begged my parents for more pencils, pens and sketchbooks I wanted to create what I refused to say. Every pencil stroke was like a cut I couldn’t erase, every section I colored was like a wall blocking out the negativity, my tears ran down my face as I finished every picture. My life has become a mural of pain, suffering, redemption and the power to overcome, I made my life into something I never could see for myself. Now every stroke is one of redemption, one of power, one of forgiveness, one of great passion. I learned a lot from my parents. Both good and bad. At the end of the day I see this memory as a gift because I learned to be a quiet observer. I learned to be an artist. As an artist, I have decided to seek out ways to feel proud of the many aspects of myself that other girls like me seem to shy away from. When I think back to that day and think of my mother, I see her strength, it took a strong woman to move past that and raise me. I do not and will never see myself as a victim. I want to communicate, now and to future potential design clients, that sense of self esteem and power. My goal is to reflect dark skin full of rich and glowing melanin, curly coarse black hair that nobody is willing to embrace, and bodies with full hips and lips and curves. I want to be proud of my melanin, to look into the mirror and see a queen staring back at me.

shop.title: Vanessa Lara Avalos
shop.description: I am 19 years old. I am a freshman at the Milwaukee Institute of Art and Design. I started my career since I have been in high school. In early 2018, I was in a contest for photography through Zip Mke, and in September of 2018, I won and had one of the pictures I had taken featured and permanently displayed in the Fiserv Forum. In 2019, I was one of the students to win an honorable mention for Scholastics Art and Writing Awards, for the Corn Husk dress piece featured. My work is heavily influenced by Mexican culture, and I love the vibrant colours, stories and the richness of the culture itself. I have strong ties to the culture since all of my family was born in Mexico, only me and my sisters are US-born. I am a 1st generation Mexican-American, and I believe it is important for me to embrace my roots. Through my work I like to depict the beauty and richness of the culture, I like to educate those who are not exposed to it and see it as “foreign”. I believe it is more important now to embrace my roots in the heat of the moment as we see the rise of hate and division within the country. I like to deliver a strong message saying, “I am here, I exist, and I’m what makes America too”. Images can have tremendous power, for me, art gives me a voice and it helps me give voices for those who cannot be heard.

shop.title: Allison Westbrook
shop.description: Milwaukee born and bred with a love of science fiction and fantasy.

shop.title: Oliver Hayes
shop.description: Oliver Hayes is an up and coming non-binary artist in the Milwaukee art community. Oliver uses mixed media to achieve the unique imagery of their work. Known for their attention to detail, Oliver's artistry leaves the eye looking for the next aspect of the piece. Their black and white ink works showcase this quality as the viewer identifies each individual stroke of the pen. Often using ink and paint in their art, Hayes develops an array of color that compliments the piece's focal point. You can find their work documented on their instagram

shop.title: Trotter Alexander
shop.description: Trotter Alexander, albeit eighteen years old, exemplifies a maturity that transcends far beyond his years.He has been creating art ever since he could hold a pencil. There is no linear definition to his body of work, as every piece is layered with intricate techniques and philosophical meaning Throughout Trotters life, he has overcome many obstacles, which are embedded in the foundation of his art pieces. He used his pain as a source of inspiration to create surreal and abstract pieces of work; for the sole purpose of empowering others like him. He has found inspiration from artists Hebru Brantley and Demetrius Harmon; two black men whose art positively inspires the masses while manifesting the struggles of African Americans in America. Like them, Trotter seeks to be a relatable source of hope for his generation. Based on his portfolio, Trotter has been awarded: a position in the Global Classmates Ambassador program where only six students nationwide were selected. Trotter proudly shared with the politicians that his mission was to help change the world through his art; and during his eight days in Washington D.C. his art was displayed and served as a source of conversation for international diplomats and other political figures. Moreover, Trotter has sold numerous art pieces that remain on display at Evanston Township High School. He was awarded the Presidential Scholarship, the highest award granted at Milwaukee Institute of Art and Design, where he currently attends. In addition to these awards, Trotter has attended programs at Chicago Art Institute, Evanston Arts and Cultural Center. Trotter has worked closely alongside artists such as Raymond A. Thomas, Ceazar Perez (Czr Prz) and Khalilah Birdsong to further hone his skills.

shop.title: Laura Easey-Jones
shop.description: Award winning artist Laura Easey-Jones received her Art degree from Loyola Marymount University. She works in painting, mixed media and teaches oil and acrylic painting as well as mixed media classes.

shop.title: Julie San Felipe
shop.description: Living traditions of my ancestors, my watercolors on cut paper reflect a love of the dance, language, and songs of Ireland, but dwelling in Wisconsin, I am also influenced by our local nature, spirits, and contemporary poets. In my paintings, the entwined figures and calligraphy flirt between dreams and reality, drift over and under, tell tales, explore symbolism, yoga, and humor. With various groups, solo shows, and competitions, I have won awards and shown my work in SE Wisconsin, Madison, and Chicago galleries.

shop.title: Jeff Zimpel
shop.description: Jeff Zimpel is an artist and educator who is currently pursuing his MFA in Community Art and Social Engagement at the University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee. Zimpel graduated with his BFA in Graphic Design from Cardinal Stritch University in 2009. After teaching design at the high school level for six years he returned to his alma mater for a two-year artist residency, called Create Space MKE. In 2019 Zimpel received the G.O.L.D. Alumni Award from Cardinal Stritch University. He is currently working as an adjunct instructor in the Stritch Art department and collaborates with numerous arts and educational organizations throughout the Greater Milwaukee Area.

shop.title: Ana Edwards
shop.description: I am a Multidisciplinary Artist originally from Theodore,AL. I currently live and reside in Milwaukee,WI as a student at the Milwaukee Institute of Art and Design. When using photography, I have been focusing on language, conversation, and interaction with, and between, people and objects. I strongly believe language takes the form of text but also visually. I utilize color, angles, and lighting to covey emotion and context to my audience. 'Writing' with a camera is an important way for me to engage with the outside world and navigating language in my everyday life as well.

shop.title: Tom Kiebzak
shop.description: Tom's forty-plus years of experience as a photographer, jazz flugelhorn player, writer and abstract painter have given him the opportunity to travel the world, capturing vivid still life, nature and cultural images. Starting with 35mm film, eventually graduating to 2 1/4 then 4x5 and now in the digital world, Tom has had featured photos published in web sites, brochures, gallery exhibits, posters, CD covers, and cover/feature story photos for various publications. Tom brings a wide array of experience as a studio, event, landscape photographer, and educational artist-in-residence. "As the images of other photographers have inspired me to explore the world, I hope that my own contributions will inspire others to do the same, finding new perspectives and insights in their own mind's eye."

shop.title: Rosie Brandenburg
shop.description: Milwaukee fine artist, miad grad, biracial woman paints big demon ladies as a way to reach to into my subconscious and soothe the trauma of the past. My characters and self portraits find themselves on torn tattered textured black surfaces while their usually colorful and eccentric appearance is the only thing lighting their path. My work is mainly an exploration of myself and for far I can stretch my own thoughts and spiralling.

shop.title: kowalczykart
shop.description: John Kowalczyk describes his art as "shrine-like, shiny, symmetrical, and seductive figurations that become maps of my mind combining myth, math, and magic." His work is comprised of mixed media paintings, sculptures, and larger than life installations that incorporate vintage fabrics, thrift store treasures, gift wrap, shelf liner, string, ribbon, repurposed drawings, glitter and gold. The collaged elements of his artwork become more than the sum of their parts exhibiting a spiritual nature. Born in Chicago in 1988, John Kowalczyk currently lives and works in Milwaukee, WI as an artist who utilizes art as a vehicle towards a more equitable society. He received his BFA in painting from Milwaukee Institute of Art and Design in 2010, and began a three year residency with RedLine Milwaukee soon after, where he curated gallery exhibitions and developed a passion for community art. Since 2017, Kowalczyk has served as the Program Director with the non profit organization Artists Working in Education where he oversees large scale community art projects working with artists, community stakeholders, and youth in Milwaukee. Kowalczyk founded the company Brick and Beauty in 2019 which produces custom visual art experiences and mural work. Kowalczyk’s work has been exhibited at the Sienna Art Institute in Italy, The Charles Allis Art Museum, The Museum of Wisconsin Art, Cedarburg Cultural Center, John Michael Kohler Art Center, and D.Varelli Gallery in Chicago along with other galleries across the U.S. Kowalczyk is represented by Scout Gallery in Milwaukee, WI.

shop.title: Amanda Rubi
shop.description: Hola, I'm Amanda Rubi and I'm a long time crafty person with a passion for visual arts and painting. I primarily work with acrylic paint on canvas but I've been experimenting with incorporating texture and depth into my works lately with things like fabric and yarn. I would say my style is mostly pop-art using bright colors and interesting textures but I have interests in illustration and creative writing as well. In addition to being an artist and team member of TRUE Skool I also have a professional background in marketing. My goal with my works of art, is to continue to grow my skills, process my emotions and spread joy to others.

shop.title: Ron Dunn
shop.description: Ron Dunn is a versatile and talented illustrator, artist and designer. He has worked for years in the fields of graphic design and fine art, but illustration is his true passion and expertise. A distinguishing characteristic of Ron’s work is portraiture and gritty realism. There are few in the field of illustration who can capture a likeness as well as Ron. He prides himself on revealing the “essence” of a subject, going beyond what is shown in a typical photo.

shop.title: Cordelia Ellis
shop.description: Raised in Milwaukee Wisconsin and a graduate of UW-Milwaukee Self Taught artist—forever student of the craft Mediums: Acrylic, Stretched Canvas, various strokes “I believe in range and allowing my emotions to spill on the canvas or paper—if doodling. What I paint varies. It’s just my dreams in a form for the world to see

shop.title: Ken Brown
shop.description: • Artist Ken Brown was born and raised in Milwaukee, Wisconsin. He attended public schools earned his Bachelor's degree in Business Administration from Kentucky State University. He followed his heart and chose teaching art as a career. His work is exhibited widely in public and private collections. His work can be seen in Milwaukee's Black Cat Alley, an outdoor space featuring over 20 worldclass large scale murals. Ken Brown is best known for his signature stained glass painting style. These highly intricate works have gained the attention of art lovers and collector around the globe. In addition to painting Ken also writes poetry, sculpts, and plays keyboard. He lives and works in Milwaukee as a professional muralist, portrait artist, and instructor.

shop.title: Shakaylen Rodgers
shop.description: My name is Shakaylen Rodgers and I am an artist. Art for me has become about my legacy. I wanted to make pieces that’ll live on after I’m gone. Art that’ll make my daughter proud that her mom made this. Art is a way for me to express all the things I stand for as far as me being black, a woman, a mother and also a Christian. Art allows me to express these things on so many different levels. I have been painting seriously for about 2 years now. It’s very difficult for me to describe my art because once I put my brush to the canvas all of my thoughts just go away. My art is carefree and very open to interpretation. As an upcoming artist in the inner city I take so much pride in just setting my pieces in my front yard and seeing so many people showing interest in my art. I believe pieces of my art are in many homes being taken care of with love. My dream is to paint for as long as I can and to reach as many people as I can.

shop.title: Zakia Wells
shop.description: I am a Milwaukee born and raised artist Zaw Trance also known as Zakia Wells. My art focuses on women, spirituality and working through trauma. I love to play with color and paint strokes to express emotion in my paintings. I always say, if my art connects to you; it is meant for you to have because you must share a bond with what you see; it needs you too.

shop.title: Byada Meredith
shop.description: Hello everyone, my name is Byada - I was born on an island near Thailand.  I lived on my family farm and while growing up I wrote stories and danced and worked and made art. I got a little taller and became a more full-time artist between high school and college.  My university was a school that specialized in art and architecture, and I graduated from there with a degree in print-making and learned many traditional and modern techniques.  After university, I painted murals in Thai temples for a while and then worked as an art teacher and also graphic designer for a big company.  Working for a big company was good for the bills, but sometimes it was difficult to make the art that was in your heart.   I painted and made the sculptures in this time, had some art shows locally and in Japan, and also opened a manga store in Bangkok.  After a lot of ups and downs, life took me across the ocean to a new home. I moved to America 10 years ago and opened up a clothing and Art store and now I am working on starting my own Gallery and shop. Fast forward a bit, add a bunch of hard work and super chilly winters, and now I am a citizen and Milwaukeean! I am working with Black Cat Alley and other mural groups and Im excited to be a part of the community of Art in our city!

shop.title: Yamilex Borges
shop.description: Hello, my name is Yami. I recently took up painting as a hobby. I most enjoy doing scenery paintings but I hope to soon evolve my skills and explore new forms of painting.

shop.title: Arts@Large
shop.description: Arts @ Large activates Milwaukee’s communities to build environments that support arts-rich, lifelong learning. Submitted works were created by students in partnership with some of Milwaukee's most engaging Artist Educators.

shop.title: Mikal Floyd-Pruitt
shop.description: Mikal Floyd-Pruitt is a multi-disciplinary artist whose works include paintings, sculptures, modified clothing items, and found-object assemblages. After graduating Harvard University in 2006 Floyd-Pruitt moved his art practice back to Milwaukee, where he grew up. Floyd-Pruitt started rapping and producing music as a youth, taking up the moniker MC Mikal. These early forays into making music led to his first collaborations with other artists. Along with his personal art practice, he is also a community artist and cultural producer. His involvement includes “putting together projects with youth groups, serving as creative consultant on various public art projects, and going into organizations to help them accomplish an idea.” “As an artist I take a multifaceted approach to creating. I studied filmmaking in college, taught myself to paint, took some screen-printing classes, dabbled in a bit of sculpture, and essentially when I think of something, I try to figure out how to make it,” said Floyd-Pruitt. “It’s all sort of one creative mash-up for me.” Floyd-Pruitt is currently engaged in hip-hop-focused projects, inspired by such artists as producer J Dilla, and rapper Ghostface Killah, a former member of Wu Tang Klan. His work was featured in a larger installation series exhibited at Jazale’s Art Studio in Bronzeville at the end of 2016. “We did a series called Art House Trap. The intent was to create a free, intergenerational community event, where people were welcome to experience the creative process and participate in a discussion about hip-hop,” Floyd-Pruitt said. “I have a lot of recording to do, and I’m excited about my next body of work. Hip hop, liberation, jilted youth, I’m about that.” “I also rep I AM MILWAUKEE,” said Floyd-Pruitt, referring to the logo he designed and trademarked. “It’s a lifestyle brand promoting unity, creativity, pride and ownership in Milwaukee.” The brand offers apparel, and is going to expand soon to develop media to showcase the city’s creativity and talent, he said. “I’m from Milwaukee; I grew up here. After I graduated from college I came back here and to me it’s my home. It’s important to me to see the art market and the culture develop and expand and I think it’s a challenge worth taking on.” -Partial text from an article on Milwaukee Neighborhood News Service by Mitchell Mittelstedt, published on June 5, 2017.

JupiterAllen is an extension of the Divine to ingest, digest, invest, and release...we invite you to join us​LOVE

shop.title: David Kasir
shop.description: David Najib Kasir, a Syrian-American artist based in Milwaukee is best known for his contemporary oil paintings. Featuring common themes of family, love, life, and loss, he offers a look into his own life through his artwork. Kasir sat with the Wisconsin Muslim Journal to discuss his inspirations, cultural identity, and how the two merge on the canvas through a unique and colorful geometric design style.

shop.title: Luther Hall
shop.description: ​ Born and raised in Milwaukee, Wisconsin, Luther Hall (a.k.a. Mistaloo Meff) is a multitalented visual and performing artist/activist. After receiving his degree in 1997 from Hampton University in Graphic Design he has completed one year of study at Madison Media Institute for video game design. He has used his talent as a professional freelance graphic designer for over 20 years. After several years of experience as an educator in both public and private schools his focus has been towards developing artistic expression in young people. Guided by a passion for learning both traditional and technological artistic method, his latest works are a characteristic representation of current social and ideological issues.

shop.title: Anisa Garcia
shop.description: I'm a self taught artist in Milwaukee, WI. I've been painting for 4 years now and also starting to customize clothing.

shop.title: Anna Alicia Rodriguez
shop.description: Anna Alicia Rodriguez is an illustrator born and raised in Milwaukee, WI. Her influences are primarily turn of the century artists like Aubrey Beardsley, Edward Gorey, and Arthur Rackham. Her work is often a glorification of local artists and admirable members of creative society, as well as mythological gods and saints. Rodriguez’s style has an air of unpolished folk art, which brings charm to its reverent subject matter. She also enjoys writing fiction and often incorporates literary motifs in her art.

shop.title: Michael Vargas
shop.description: My name is Michael Vargas I'm 27 years old from Miami,Fl. My paintings are painted in layers of acrylic paint to form textures

shop.title: Emmanuel Jimenez
shop.description: Milwaukee based graphic designer with a penchant for illustration based design. His works tend to fluctuate between playful and colorful to a more dark and mysterious atmosphere. There is no real concise thematic, but rather an amalgamation of experiences, interests and feelings. What hides beneath the surface is a desire to keep growing artistically every day. (I haven't really been doing a lot of traditional based art recently, but I do want to get back at it especially painting & inking.)

shop.title: Samantha Grosenick
shop.description: Carroll University graduate of 2019 that enjoys exploring a variety of medium. Sam loves using a variety a music references, vibrant colors, and texture in her works.

shop.title: Ashley Prosken
shop.description: Ashley Prosken is a Chicago based artist that has been creating art since she was a child. She enjoys learning new medias and what new challenges that they provoke. She has learned a range of mediums such as, drawing, painting, sculpture and photography, but she always finds her comfort with a canvas and brush in hand. As her education and skills developed more as she grows older, there have always been some common themes in her work, such as duality and phycological elements. One of her favorite subjects to work with, no matter the medium, is the human figure. The nude figure can evoke a psychological connection to an audience and can calm the mind of the artist. As she continues developing her art she will pursue searching for a career in the arts where she will feel most at home.

shop.title: Elisabeth Bates
shop.description: life is meant to not only be enjoyed but expressed.

shop.title: George Jones
shop.description: GeorgeDavid Jones is a interdisciplinary producer, artist, composer, musician, performer, builder, farmer and writer. George has been exposed to the arts for as long as he can remember. Using his philosophy of "soft focus," over the years, he has creatively interpreted his relationship to the human, natural, emotional and spiritual landscapes he resides. Texture, time and space, distance and spontaneity permeates his work and helps define the narrative. Creatively reusing and repurposing refuse material into functional art and design is his current passion.

shop.title: ahlersjaque0
shop.description: Jaq is my name Digital collages are my game. I love mixing beauty and chaos into a cohesive yet eye catching piece. I pride myself on my self expression & love provoking new unexplored thoughts with my work

shop.title: Stephanie Krellwitz
shop.description: Stephanie is an independent artist and yoga instructor in the Milwaukee area. She works primarily in paint with pieces ranging from miniatures to mural designs.

shop.description: Islands of Brilliance is neurodiverse talent accelerator and virtual community using art, design & STEM learning opportunities to connect with and engage youth and young adults living with autism.
